Seven people died
and five others sustained serious injuries after a trailer collided with a 14-seater matatu at Governor's area on theÂ Bomet-Narok road on Friday morning. According
to a police report seen by Citizen Digital, the driver of the trailer heading to Bomet from Narok lost control of the vehicle after
one of its right front tires burst leading to a head-on collision with the oncoming matatu. The survivors were rushed to Narok Referral Hospital while the bodies of the
deceased were moved to the
Hospital's mortuary.  The wreckage of the vehicles were towed to Narok
Police Station.